===Etymology===
Reasoning that {{zh-l|嵩|tr=-}} and {{zh-l|崧}} are the same word and the latter's phonetic {{och-l|松}} suggests the medial *''-l-'', {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} minimally reconstructs Old Chinese pronunciation *''suŋ'' < *''sluŋ'', proposes that it was from {{der|zh|aav}} and compares it to {{cog|mkh-pro|*slu(u)ŋ|*sluŋ ~ *sluuŋ|high}}. However, note {{zh-ref|Baxter & Sagart (2014)}}'s reconstructions {{zh-l|*嵩}} ~ {{och-l|崧|tr=*[s]uŋ}}, & {{och-l|松|tr=*sə.ɢoŋ}} without medial *''-l-''.

